Build Challenge We're starting out 2020 with some great tunes (not tuna ) and we want you to help make an amazing music box with your favorite song in it! Use those note blocks, build an amazing structure, and help us jam out while getting your favorite song stuck in everyone else’s head! Music Box - January 24 to February 7 Guidelines: Must be built in Minecraft Earth This should be a brand new build and not be something that you've already built Build plate size will not matter & won't be a factor in judging Feel free to ask for advice pertaining to your build in #music-box-challenge All work must be done by one individual Remember, this is for fun only If it's a submission picture, please feel free to ask a moderator to pin it. Winning submissions may be used in social media (edited)

cLOVEpod February 7, 2020 at 3:49 PM (UTC-08:00)
Welcome to the BOOM ROOM! Tonight DJ Carrie R. Current debuts her explosive new remix of a 1980’s arcade favorite! (Watch your head…) I used mine carts to trigger and control looping sequences of note blocks, which can be seen best in the build mode video. I couldn’t come up with a way to end the loops so I used TNT to halt them, because explosions are fun The build is a nightclub in an old warehouse. Unfortunately both the bartender and DJ wanted to wander out of their areas so I had to lower their floors a bit to keep them safe. The DJ’s name is a reference to Carrier Current, which is a method of transmitting radio signals along rail lines. https://youtu.be/c4n_1y6Ob28 https://youtu.be/GZu1nTv9nqE
